                        <note>
                           The exhortation <q xml:lang="gez">ንግድፍ፡ እምላዕሌነ፡ ኵሎ፡ ምግባረ፡ ጽልመት፡ ወንልበስ፡ ወልታ፡ ብርሃን፡ በከመ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ በውስተ፡ መልዕክቱ፡</q> is added on 
                           <locus target="#37v"/>.
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.33">
                        <title>Excerpt from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3509Epistle">First Epistle of John</ref> 2:27-3:1</title>
                        <note>
                           The invocation <q xml:lang="gez">ዮሐንስ፡ ድንግል፡ በአምሳለ፡ ትጉሃን፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ድንግል፡ ምክሐ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ሥርግው፡ በቀጸላ፡ ስን፡</q> is added on 
                           <locus target="#38r"/>.
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.34">
                        <title>Excerpt from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1019Actsof">Gǝbra ḥawāryāt</ref> 5:27-32</title>
                        <note>
                           The passage <q xml:lang="gez">ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ብርሃናተ፡ ዓለም፡ ሱቱፋነ፡ ሕማም፡ ሐዋርያተ፡ ሰላም፡ አስራበ፡ ምሕረት፡ 
                                 <sic>ከዓው፡</sic>
                               
                           እምአርያም፨</q> is added on <locus target="#38v"/>.
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.35">
                        <locus to="39v"/>
                        <title>Excerpt from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1693John">Gospel of John</ref> 20:1-18</title>
                        <note>
                           The excerpt concludes on <locus target="#39v"/> with an invocation to the day of the resurrection, which begins as follows: 
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡ ዕለተ፡ ብርሃን፡ ወፀዳል፡ ሰንበተ፡ ምሥጢር፡ ርእሰ፡ መዋዕል፡
                           </q>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="40r" to="44v"/>
                     <title type="complete">Prayers to Our Lady Mary</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.1">
                        <locus from="40r"/>
                        <title type="complete">Short invocation to Our Lady Mary</title>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                           ጸሎተ<supplied reason="omitted">ነ</supplied>፡ ወስእለተነ፡ ማርያም፡ ባርኪ፡ ወኪያነኒ፡ እሞተ፡ ሙስና፡ መሐኪ፡
                        </incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.2">
                        <locus from="40v" to="39r"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3124HymnMary">Malkǝʾ-hymn to Our Lady Mary</title>
                        <note>The text terminates abruptly, possibly due to a material loss.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="45r" to="48v"/>
                     <title type="incomplete">እግዚኦ፡ ተሣሀል፡ ለነ፡</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፡ እምድኅረ፡ 
                           <sic>ወንግል፡</sic>
                         
                        
                           <sic>ወያንሥእ፡</sic>
                         ሕዝብ፡ ወይብሉ፡ እግዚኦ፡ መሐረነ። ጸልዩ። በእንተ፡ 
                        ጽንዓ፡ ዛቲ፡ መካን፡ ወኵሎሙ፡ መካናት፡
                     </incipit>
                     <note>The text is acephalous, possibly because of a material loss. 
                        It includes <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4711Mastabqwe">Mastabqʷǝʿān</ref>: prayers for the sick, for the pilgrims, for the fruit of the earth, for the sleepers, for the king, for the 
                        catechumens, for the peace, for the Church.
                     </note>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                      ገብረ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ በብዝኃ፡ ሣህሉ፡ ወምሕረቱ። ኪርያ፡ ለይሶን፡ ፫ጊዜ፡ እምኖዲ፡ ናይናን፡ ኪርያ፡ ታዖስ፡ ናይናን፡ ኪርያ፡ ፯፫ጊዜ፡ ማስያስ፡ ናይ፡ ኪር<supplied reason="omitted">ያ</supplied>፡ 
                        ፫ጊዜ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ናይ፡ ኪር<supplied reason="omitted">ያ</supplied>፡ ፯፫ጊዜ፡ ክርስቶ<supplied reason="omitted">ስ</supplied>፡ ናይ፡ 
                        ኪር<supplied reason="omitted">ያ</supplied>፡ አማኑኤል፡ ናይ፡ ኪር<supplied reason="omitted">ያ</supplied>።
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="48v" to="52"/>
                     <title type="complete">On the computation</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                        
                           <sic>ሐሳበ፡</sic>
                         ርቱዕ፡ እንተ፡ እምኀበ፡ ይቀርብ፡ በ፲፩አበቅቴ፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፱ለመስከረም፡ መጥቅዕ፡
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                        ወዘተረፈከ፡ እም፬፡ ውእቱኬ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ፩ለእመ፡ ተረፈከ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ፪ለእመ፡ ተረፈከ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ፫ለእመ፡ ተረፈከ፡ ሉቃስ፡ ፬ለእመ፡ ተረፈከ፡ ዮሐንስ።  
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                     <locus from="52r" to="54r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3088RepCh368">ʾO-rǝḫrǝḫta ḫǝllinā</title>
                     <note>
                        The hymn is followed by a short invocation to Our Lady Mary:
                        <q xml:lang="gez">
                           <supplied reason="omitted">ሰ</supplied>ላም፡ ሰላም፡ ለመልክ<supplied reason="omitted">ዕ</supplied>ኪ፡ ኵሉ፡ እምነ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ወወርኅ፡ ዘያበርኅ፡ ስነ፡ ፀዳሉ። 
                           ስብሐት፡ ወክብር፡ ለመንግሥትኪ፡ ይደሉ፡ እስመ፡ አባልኪ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ አባሉ፡ ማርያም፡ በረከትኪ፡ ምስሌነ፡ የሀሉ።
                        </q>.
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
          
